description: Kieran Humphreys and three others are due in court over the death of Archie Woodbridge.
title: Man charged with murder of six-month-old baby
title_page: Man charged with murder of six-month-old baby in Houghton Regis - BBC News
maintext:
A man has been charged with murder over the death of a six-month-old baby.
Bedfordshire Police were called to an address in Houghton Regis at 17:30 GMT on 9 February 2024 over concerns for the welfare of a baby.
Archie Woodbridge was taken to hospital, where he later died.
Kieran Humphreys, 32, of Bromley Gardens, Houghton Regis, has been remanded in custody to appear at Luton Crown Court on Friday.
